<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-02-03T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-02-03T18:00:00-05:00" n="205" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d205">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">715.1715/1390: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Representative of the President</hi>
                                    (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Corrigan</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Panama</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-02-03T18:00:00-05:00">February 3, 1939—6 p.m.</date>
                                    <lb/> [Received February 4—12:32 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>15. At a conference in the Legation this afternoon the President of
                                the Commission drafted a note for the Honduran Government. The note
                                gives assurance that no juridical question is involved and again
                                asks for cooperation in making the necessary geographic studies. I
                                agreed to the general tenor of the note which will be submitted to
                                the Venezuelan member before being despatched by Zúñiga Montúfar
                                after his return to Costa Rica tomorrow.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Corrigan</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>